result.execSummary:
Jasmine A Williams was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jasmine A Williams was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jasmine A Williams not in court.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: tmk.
Defendant has been turned over to the State of Texas. On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.
Status conference scheduled for 05-15-2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Jasmine A Williams in court with attorney Anne M Jaspers.  Defendant Jasmine A Williams in custody.  Ronald Dague appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Court reviewed complaint and found probably cause.  Defendant is eligible for Public Defender representation.

Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Texas.  Defendant waived extradition hearing and consents to extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant remanded into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department and awaiting pick up by the State of Texas.  
Court orders case adjourned to make sure that the requesting state has picked up the defendant.  Case continued to 05-15-2015 at 8:30 a.m. Branch ICCR to make sure that the requesting state picked up the defendant.
